The “Pirates of the Caribbean” actor opened up to The Sunday Times in a new interview, which focuses on his latest film, “Minamata.” In the interview, Johnny got candid about his status in Hollywood. “Some films touch people and this affects those in ‘Minamata’ and people who experience similar things. THE LIES AMBER HEARD’S PERPETRATED IN COURT

INTRO:  A relationship that started as a romantic and endearing relationship quickly turned violent and messy. From being Hollywood's favorite couple to being one of the worst and most toxic couples to be in the spotlight. The pair are still at it with their ongoing court battles and lawsuits and we are about to witness Amber’s behavior towards most of it. 

But before we head on to the video, please don’t forget to hit the like button! And if you’re new here, do smash the subscribe button down below to see more from our channel! Now on to the story:

Amber Heard and Johnny Depp are inarguably some of the most recognizable faces in Hollywood today – and they’ve gotten even more recognizable and notable in recent years though it’s all for the wrong reasons. But to keep you guys in the loop, here’s a refresher of how a seemingly promising relationship went downhill after just one year of being married to each other. “Working with Johnny was torture. It was better than I ever imagined, which is really saying something,” she told Vogue magazine once. They didn’t quite hit it off just yet as Johnny was still in a tight-knit, 14-year relationship with Vanessa Paradis with which he has also shared two children. Moreover, Amber was also dating her former partner at the time, Taysa van Ree. But it wasn’t until 2012 that the two would eventually decide to break up with who they were with and start a new relationship altogether.

It is worth mentioning though that prior to dating, Amber had been arrested in 2009 on the charge of physically assaulting van Ree in Washington. So, I guess Johnny always had the red flags? Who knows? But anyway, it wasn’t long until they were dubbed as the new it-couple of Hollywood. They eventually tied the knot in 2015 in a private ceremony held in their LA home. People were even wishing to have the same kind of relationship they had shown everyone that time.  But little did we know that there was more dark stuff happening in the background than what we’ve been led on to believe. 

But as mentioned, one year into the relationship, all hell broke loose and Amber eventually filed for divorce from Johnny and stated that she had been physically and emotionally abused by the “Pirates of the Caribbean” actor. Everything came crashing down for both parties where speculations and assertions were made especially on Depp. Under many deliberations against him, she claims Johnny threw a phone at her face that caused bruises. Meanwhile, Johnny completely and consistently denies all assertions regarding physical abuse. Apparently, after investigations were made it was proven that her claims were false and that the photos of her bruises were all made up. Moreover, the actress also claimed mental abuse on Johnny’s part saying he was using his sexes to cause her pain and suffering. However, Johnny’s exes denied all of this and even went on to come into his defense. “The idea that he is an incredibly violent person is the farthest thing from the Johnny I knew and loved. I cannot wrap my head around these accusations,” Winona Ryder narrated.

snippet.title: Novinkový mix: Hollandova budoucnost v MCU, Depp vs Amber či možné obsazení do druhé Duny
snippet.description:
Objednej si BOMBY a zadej slevový kód TOREN
https://bombashop.cz/?ref=toren

00:00 Úvod a připomínka kampaně na animovaného Spider-mana.
01:47 Tom Holland v novém rozhovoru o budoucnosti Spider-mana, své herecké vyčerpanosti a dalších detailech + souhrn nových spekulací alá další trilogie, Miles Morales a Vulture v dalším MCU projektu.
10:45 Strážci Galaxie 3 se točí a Sly je na place!
13:40 Wakanda Forever stopuje na dva měsíce natáčení - zranění hlavní hvězdy je vážnější, než se původně myslelo.
15:13 Filmový Blade nabírá novou posilu. 
17:18 DC League of Super-Pets odhalují Supermana.
19:19 V Batmanovi se možná dočkáme jednoho záporáckého překvápka. Potenciální SPOILER, jenž může vyzradit twist! 
23:30 Star Wars bude minimálně do roku 2024 stále vést Kathleen Kennedy. Souhrn filmových "plánů" a seriálové budoucnosti + obsazení Sabine Wren do Ahsoky!
29:05 Harry Potter se vrátí ve výročním speciálu pro HBO MAX. Co můžeme očekávat?
32:16 Chystá se dokument o sporu Johnnyho Deppa a Amber Heard. Co víme?
35:46 Druhá Duna představí oblíbenou knižní postavu. A je možné, že již víme... kdo byl obsazen?
39:42 Víme kdo natočí Smrtonosnou zbraň 5. 
43:14 Chris Hemsworth je v Praze! Natáčení druhého Vyproštění je na spadnutí. Víme v jakých lokacích se bude točit.

snippet.title: The Shady Truth of Johnny Depp & Vanessa Paradis’ Love Story |⭐ OSSA
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp and Vanessa Paradis were one of the most popular celebrity couples. Johnny and Vanessa had a whirlwind romance and only three months after they started dating, she became pregnant with their daughter Lily-Rose Depp.

 Their son Jack was born three years later. Johnny Depp said in the interview that fatherhood has "changed everything". The family did their best to maintain a low-key existence, keeping their lives under the radar as much as possible. Despite his current status as a loving father, Johnny was once known for his rebellious behavior.

Paradis and Depp surprised the world when they announced they had “amicably separated” in 2012. Both had previously talked about the strain that their conflicting schedules had on their relationship. Paradis later married in 2018 after meeting French writer Samuel Benchetrit, while Depp would go on to marry actor Amber Heard in 2015. 

Vanessa always supported her ex-partner. She named claims of domestic violence against Johnny Depp are “false facts” which have been used to damage his career.

snippet.title: Jason Momoa THREATENS To Sue Amber Heard If Aquaman 2 Fails!
snippet.description:
Jason Momoa THREATENS To Sue Amber Heard If Aquaman 2 Fails!

Subscribe to Binge Watch -  http://tiny.cc/bingewatch

WATCH NEXT 👇

Celebrities React to Dave Chappelle Being Canceled

https://youtu.be/Q7wLcEHSEr8

Amber Heard ATTACKS LAPD In Court - They Fight Back…

https://youtu.be/JuOr_czN_9E

Related videos:

Jason Momoa Reveals He Sues Amber Heard If Aquaman 2 FAILS!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eTx7kRrkqGA

AMBER'S GETTING SUED - Jason Momoa Reveals He Sues Amber Heard If Aquaman 2 FAILS | The Gossipy

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cK1U35sC-PI

Despite an online campaign that called for Amber Heard removal from Aquaman 2, the actress will be playing Mera in the Aquaman sequel. Fans are upset that Amber Heard is not fired from the movie in the same way that her ex-husband Johnny Depp was dropped from the Fantastic Beasts franchise, where he had played the dark wizard Grindelwald. And now it seems that with the controversial reputation that Amber Heard has, the film has every chance of failure. And if the massive failure happens, how would Jason Momoa going to respond with his income at stake?
The divisive and public divorce between Amber Heard and Johnny Depp resulted in allegations of domestic ab*se by both parties, with Amber Heard initially winning widespread sympathy for her claims. When the whole thing started, the whole world believed Amber Heard that she was a victim and she even wrote an op-ed for Washington Post about being a domestic a*se survivor. She called herself a ‘public figure representing domestic ab*se’ and she said: ‘I feel the full force of our culture’s wrath for women who speak out’. 
But then, after Johnny Depp aired his side of the story, social media opinion swung in his favor. Moreover, many evidences proving that Amber Heard was a liar surfaced and people realized they executed the wrong person. Johnny Depp also lost a civil suit against British tabloid The Sun in a case centered on a 2018 article that referred to him as a “wife-beater.” But fans already understood who is the wolf in a sheep’s clothing. 
But Johnny Depp’s career was already over. He was fired from several roles, including the role of wizard Grindelwald in the Fantastic Beasts franchise and the Pirate Captain Jack Sparrow. He recently even spoke up about cancel culture and stated that Hollywood is boycotting him for nothing and that it is unfair that his career is ruined. 
However, Amber Heard’s career is fine. She is still a L’Oréal Paris ambassador, has been invited to huge events like Paris Fashion Week and she still plays a role of Mera in Aquaman 2. When it became clear that JD’s reputation and career is over, fans couldn’t just sit and do nothing. So, they decided to remove Amber Heard from the Aquaman 2. They created an online petition calling on Warner Bros. to remove Amber Heard from the upcoming comic book tentpole “Aquaman 2”. Despite the fact that the petition has garnered over 1.6 million signatures and was fast approaching the 2 million mark, it didn't help at all.
As for the Aquaman and the Lost Kingdom producer Peter Safran, he said the campaign had no bearing on Amber Heard’s role in the forthcoming movie, saying on Deadline’s Hero Nation podcast that he doesn’t “think we’re ever going to react to, honestly, pure fan pressure. You gotta do what’s best for the movie. We felt that if it’s James Wan, and Jason Momoa, it should be Amber Heard. That’s really what it was. One is not unaware of what is going on in the Twitter-verse, but that doesn’t mean you have to react to it or take it as gospel or accede to their wishes. You have to do what’s right for the film, and that’s really where we landed on it.”
As for Amber Heard, she said in November that she was "super excited" to return as Mera in "Aquaman 2" and she wasn’t really bothered by that petition at all. She also shared multiple photos on her Instagram preparing to the role of Mera. Here is the photo of Amber getting ready in gym for Aquaman 2. And here is another photo of Amber wearing Mera’s suit. She captioned the photo: ‘Forgot my pajamas #tbt #aquaman2’. She also addressed the protests in a statement to Entertainment Weekly when the hate comments slammed her in the face: "Paid rumors and paid campaigns on social media don't dictate [casting decisions] because they have no basis in reality".

So, now I want to know your opinion. Do you think Amber Heard’s reputation will affect Aquaman 2 movie? If so, do you think Jason Momoa will really sue her? Let me know your opinion in the comments section down below. And thanks for watching this video and don’t forget to hit that subscribe button.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Scores MAJOR WIN In Case With Amber Heard! Amber Heard Johnny Depp Lawsuit Updates!
snippet.description:
It has indeed been a great week so far for Johnny Depp fans, when he scored a huge victory in the recent events relating to his $50 million dollar defamation case against former wife Amber Heard. Just recently, a big win in Johnny Depp’s team was celebrated when the Virginian court held his case against Amber announcing that they will be looking into the missing report of donations that Amber Heard claimed to have given to a charity. That $7 million dollars that the actress had vowed to donate is actually nowhere to be found. So where has it gone? This $7 million dollars is part of Amber Heard’s divorce settlement money from Johnny when the couple officially split in 2017. So what had really been the result of these recent judge rulings and what awaits the former couple after this huge victory for Johnny Depp? Let’s find all that out in this video. But before anything else, make sure to subscribe to our channel first and hit that notification bell for more updates on the famous Johnny Depp - Amber Heard million dollar case. Now, let’s begin!

After the divorce was finalized in 2017, it might have seemed to be the end of it all. But nope, the real chaos for the former couple was just about to start. Despite all the evidence continuing to surface about Johnny and Amber’s real marriage life story, including the recorded phone call where Amber admitted to hitting Johnny, the alleged affairs of the actress with actor James Franco and mega businessman Elon Musk, which later on was somehow proven true because the two did actually date for one whole year after Amber’s divorce with Johnny, and the missing $7 million dollar’s worth of divorce settlement that was promised by the actress to be donated to charity. All these allegations and evidence against Amber Heard were all disregarded by the UK newspaper company The Sun, calling Johnny Depp a name that until now rings untrue for the actor. Because of this nickname given to him by a British tabloid, he filed for a libel case, to which he unfortunately lost. But what’s more of a bummer in that event was that Johnny lost his chance to reprise his role in the 2022 third installment of the Fantastic Beasts series. Johnny’s team defended and is continuing to claim that Amber is viewing herself to the public as a victim rather than a perpetrator. And that her allegations were part of an "elaborate hoax to generate positive publicity" for the actress. 

But lately, there has been recent progress in the Johnny Depp – Amber Heard case. As you remember, Amber Heard tried not only one, not even two, but three times to get Johnny’s defamation case to be dismissed at court, defending that Johnny Depp already lost his libel case against news publisher The Sun, so that should count, right? But the judges seem to be full of Amber’s lies too and they even warned her that she’d receive serious consequences if proven that she was just wasting the court’s time. Meanwhile, if Amber had this card with her of a lost libel case against a UK news company, but Johnny also had his own game card, and that is the missing $7 million dollars’ worth of donation from her divorce settlement with the actor. Yes, you heard that right. For Amber to prove that she was not really just after the 58 year old actor’s wealth during their marriage and split, she pledged to donate half of her divorce settlement to charity. Which she did…Kidding! No one really knows up until now where that huge sum of money went, which helped Johnny win a legal ruling from a New York judge that will force the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) to reveal how much money his ex-wife, actress Amber Heard, actually donated to them after Amber claimed that she donated half of it. Johnny and his lawyers believe that the Aquaman actress has been lying about the size of her donation, and they believe that proving that she lied will be a major factor in the upcoming suit against Amber that will make it to court in Virginia next year. The donation amounts matter because one of the reasons that the judge gave for believing Amber's version of events over Johnny's was that one of the Fantastic Beasts actor's biggest claims was that Amber only married him for his money. It is also significant as the promised donation was cited by a judge in the UK while deciding on a libel case brought about by Johnny against publishers of The Sun. In February, Amber Heard had already stated that she had donated the divorce settlement money to charity.

Johnny Depp has endured a lot so far. That’s all for today guys, if you enjoyed that video, make sure to like, subscribe, and smash that notification bell for more videos like this.

“I immediately covered my face and was crying due to the pain resulting from the phone hitting me. Johnny charged at me, insisting on seeing my face. He taunted me, challenged whether or not the telephone hit me. He then forcibly pulled back my hair as I attempted to face up from the sofa. I then yelled out ‘Call 911’ hoping it might be heard by iO who was still on the phone. Johnny continued screaming at me, pulling my hair, striking me, and violently grabbing my face,” Heard alleged

4) Samantha Spector
High-profile attorney Samantha Spector, who represented Morena Baccarin in her litigation with ex Austin Chick, is Heard’s lawyer.

“Unfortunately, this is often not the primary incident of violence perpetrated by Johnny against Amber,” Spector writes in court documents obtained by PEOPLE. “There are two other incidents within the past six months. One day after Heard claimed she was abused by Depp, de Cadenet shared a photograph of herself with Heard and model-turned-actress Amber Valletta during de Cadenet’s May 23 birthday celebration. within the photo, which has since been deleted, Heard is seen smiling but together with her hair placed over half her face.

2) Evan Rachel Wood
Who? Actress, known for True Blood, Mildred Pierce and therefore the Ides of March.
In a tweet that was later deleted, Wood seemed to criticize the way some media outlets had written about Heard's sexuality: “Amber Heard‘s sexuality is merely relevant therein bi women are at far greater risk of experiencing intimate partner violence. Bisexuality however isn't a reason for violence. It doesn’t mean Heard is somehow immoral or deserving of abuse.”

1)Andy Richter
Who? Comedy star and screenwriter, known for his work on the talk show Conan. On May 28, 2016, Richter suggested that Depp and his representatives might be attempting to fire up bad publicity for Heard.

On May 28, 2016, he tweeted that, one among the items you'll pay a publicist try to form your ex look bad within the press after you have been accused of abuse.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Filing $50M Defamation Case Against Ex Amber Heard
snippet.description: Johnny Depp will be allowed to pursue his defamation case against ex-wife Amber Heard. According to court documents obtained by Access Hollywood, a Virginia-based judge granted the "Pirates of The Caribbean" actor permission to move forward with his 50-million-dollar lawsuit. On August 17, 2021 the court overruled Amber's supplemental plea, which she filed in an attempt to get the case dismissed. The 58-year-old is suing his ex over an op-ed she wrote for the Washington post in 2018.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Amber Heard Sentenced After Exposed For Fake Photos…
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Sentenced After Exposed For Fake Photos…

snippet.title: Amber Heard encourages women to 'stand up for yourself' and 'speak your mind'
snippet.description:
(3 Oct 2021) AMBER HEARD ENCOURAGES WOMEN TO 'STAND UP FOR YOURSELF' AND 'SPEAK YOUR MIND'
Amber Heard says empowerment is "being able to live your truth, to stand up for yourself, to speak your mind." 
The Hollywood star was speaking Sunday (3OCT21) in Paris ahead of L'Oreal's fashion show, which is dedicated to women's empowerment.
Heard is a spokesperson for the cosmetics company, which has launched a campaign to encourage women and men to intervene safely if they experience or witness street harassment.
Heard says that harassment on the street is something "women especially have almost come to take for granted as just normal."
"If women and girls all over the world cannot feel safe just walking on the street, how do we expect to carry demands or expectations of equality and respect into a workplace or into a home?" she says.
The actor, who is currently shooting "Aquaman 2" in London, was accompanied by her baby girl, Oonagh Paige.
The 35-year-old star says having a daughter has been "the most beautiful gift" she's ever experienced.
"It has definitely recalibrated my perspective on literally every aspect of my, of my world, but especially being a woman, raising a girl to be a woman. It's never been more important to advocate on behalf of female empowerment and women's rights in general. Equality in general, because I want her to have and inherit, come into a world in which she is free to walk down the street without harassment, in which she can carry that sort of freedom with her when she chooses to wear makeup or not wear makeup when she chooses to enter a work-place or work force."
Asked whether she would encourage her daughter to following in her footsteps as an actor, Heard said "I can't even begin to unpack all the problems with my industry for women."
Adding, "but I will support her in whatever she hopes to do and wants to do."

snippet.title: How Amber Heard Ruined Her Own Career
snippet.description:
10 Times Johnny Depp Tried To Warn Us About Amber Heard
https://youtu.be/n2q-kN4GIwg

Amber heard has been the CENTER OF ATTENTION of many controversies since her NASTY DIVORCE with The Rum Diary co-star and the popular Hollywood celebrity Johnny Depp! The actress who has been a part of the Warner Bros and DC universe Aquaman, the spokesperson of cosmetics brand L’Oreal Paris, as well as American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) ambassador for women's rights has been getting NEGATIVE responses and STRONG HATE and it seems that she might have ruined her OWN CAREER! 
In fact, if sources are to be believed the actress may not appear in the second installment of DC’s Aquaman that will be released in 2022! And according to multiple websites the actress has been replaced by Games of thrones star EMILIA CLARKE!!! In today’s video I will reveal how Amber Heard destroyed her own Hollywood career in her attempts to defame Johnny Depp! But before jumping in the video you can help our channel grow by smashing those like, subscribe and bell notification buttons. A little action from you can help grow our channel tremendously!
And make sure to stick with us till the end of this video!

Amber Heard’s career started in 2003 when she first appeared in two music videos Kenny Chesney's 'There Goes My Life' and Eisley's 'I Wasn't Prepared," and went onto star in an array of TV shows and movies, her career really took off in 2015 the same year when she married Depp and when she had prominent roles in four mainstream movies. 
She played the lead in the comedy-drama 'Magic Mike XXL,' which like its predecessor, 'Magic Mike' (2012), was a huge box office success. Heard also starred in the critically acclaimed historical drama 'The Danish Girl' and the independent crime thriller 'The Adderall Diaries.' She also appeared in the television film 'One More Time.'
Although she appeared in different television shows and a few movies but she was not in any way equivalent to Johnny Depp in fame or standing in Hollywood. After she married Depp her position in Hollywood solidified and she started getting more recognition. After her divorce from Depp she landed the biggest role of her career in the form of WARNER BROS Aquaman in which she played the character of female lead MERA alongside Justin Momoa. 'Aquaman' became the fifth most profitable release of 2018, and the most profitable DCEU installment till that point.
At that time she also got selected as the brand ambassador of LOREAL PARIS and became the representative of women rights in ACLU! She got these opportunities after she blamed Depp with domestic violence accusations and pretended to be a victim. This earned her a lot of support and she became successful.  L'Oreal announced in 2017 that Heard will be the new global spokesperson, calling her "fearless, witty and smart" and a woman who defied definition and rejected convention. 
And yet, she has claimed in her court declaration countering ex-husband's $50 million defamation suit against her that her career took a serious hit and she received death threats that forced her to constantly keep on changing her contact details.
"Following my highly-publicized separation from Johnny, I read accounts in the media referring to me as a victim of domestic violence. In response, many people called me a liar (without ever hearing my story). I was dropped from a global fashion brand's upcoming campaign. I lost a part of a movie in which I had already been cast. People I have never met or spoken to threatened me with violence. I received so many death threats I had to change my phone number on a near-weekly basis," she declared in her motion to dismiss the 'Pirates of the Caribbean' actor's lawsuit filed in Fairfax County, Virginia Circuit Court.

But things started changing when new evidences came to light! Initially most of the people were supporting Amber in her fight against Depp but when audio and video tapes of Amber Heard threatening Depp were released many people were shocked and furious at Heard!
Ever since the verdict of the Libel case was announced by the UK court, millions of Johnny Depp fans are criticizing  the "Aquaman" actress. His fans recently started circulating a video featuring Amber Heard as a proof that although she has won the legal battle but people still hate the "Aquaman" actress. The video is an interview of the actress posted on YouTube channel "Access" with more than one million followers.
The video has received only 16,000 likes while it has been disliked by more than 203,000 people. Posted on December 15, the YouTube video was watched by over a million people within 10 days.

Thank you for your valuable time, if you are interested into these kind of stuff, please consider subscribing to our channel and support my hard work if you enjoy watching our videos regularly.

SUBSCRIBE:  https://bit.ly/30kR4eB

snippet.title: Elon Musk's first wife describes their relationship
snippet.description:
Elon Musk has been divorced three times, twice by the same person, and has been with
other women. However, his first wife recently opened up about the illustrious billionaire,
and what she revealed will shock many people!
In this video, we dive into the juicy bits as Musk's first wife, Justine, finally reveals what
she thinks about Elon Musk!
What better source to hear from about Elon Musk than the woman who has five of his
sons? There is a certain notoriety to being the world's richest man's ex-wife, but Justine
seems to be handling it well. She even claims she is the model ex-wife!
Justine Musk still goes by Elon's last name, which she says is for the benefit of her
children. She is a successful author who has published three fiction works; Blood Angel,
Uninvited, and a sequel to Blood Angel called Lord of Bones.
Justine was born in Ontario, Canada, and later enrolled at Queen's University in
Kingston, Canada, where she obtained a degree in English Literature. She later moved
to Japan, where she taught English, and spent time in Australia.
However, while in the university, Justine and Musk had met. Musk had obtained
Canadian citizenship through his mother. Musk eventually transferred to Wharton,
although he kept in contact with Justine.
Justine said Musk made a big impression on her by giving her his credit card to buy as
many books as she wanted and she was so impressed that they got married in 2000.
The kids came. First was Nevada, who died due to sudden infant death syndrome at the
age of ten weeks. They ended up having a set of twins and triplets, making the surviving
children between the pair five.
The couple split in 2008 with joint custody of the children, and Musk would go on to date
and marry Talulah Riley. The second marriage ended up in divorce again, but the two
decided to give it another trial by tying the knot for the second time but ultimately parting
ways again. Musk then dated Amber Heard, but the two lasted only a year due to their
intense schedules.
By 2018, Musk had been confirmed to be involved with Grimes, meaning Musk was
going back to his roots again as the artiste is Canadian. The pair have a baby together
called X but have become semi separated, although Musk recently claimed they lived
together.
One remarkable thing about all Musk's relationships is that he maintains a cordial
relationship with all his exes. For example, Musk said he and Amber Heard remains
close friends and love one another and who knows what the future holds.
And after their second and final divorce, Riley still had positive things to say about her
billionaire ex. She even made an appearance during the Strauss Rolling Stone profile of
Musk and told People magazine that she and Musk saw each other all the time and took
care of each other.
Coming back to Justine, Musk's first wife, she recently spoke about Musk where she
dropped more than a few bombshells that will change your view of the industrialist!
Previously, shortly after her divorce, Justine wrote that she watched herself slowly take
the back seat to Musk's work as Musk's success rose astronomically. She became the
trophy wife, which apparently didn't sit well with her.
But as a courtside observer to Musk's insane climb to fame, and with her skills as a
writer, Justine was able to distill the changes in her husband. While responding to a
question on Quora, she gave a rather candid impression of the man she was married to
for eight years. According to her, people like her former husband, Bill Gates, Steve
Jobs, and Richard Branson, who has a friendship with Musk, tend to be freaks and
misfits who were forced to experience the world in an unusually challenging way!
Justine claimed they don't think the way other people think but see things from angles
that unlock new ideas and insights! Other people consider them insane!
Justine illustrated Musk's childhood with the example of another friend who had a
troubled childhood because other kids mocked him for not being cool, a personae Musk
would later embrace, as you shall see! The friend's growing up was terrible enough that
he didn't want other kids going home with him from school because they threw soda
cans at him! So instead of hanging out with these mean kids, Justine's friend buried
himself in computer games and coding, leading him to his first company, which he sold
when he was in his mid twenties! But of course, nobody can throw cans at him again!
Instead, people throw money at her friend and Musk, which he welcomes

However, while in the university, Justine and Musk had met. Musk had obtained
Canadian citizenship through his mother. Musk eventually transferred to Wharton,
although he kept in contact with Justine.
Justine said Musk made a big impression on her by giving her his credit card to buy as
many books as she wanted and she was so impressed that they got married in 2000.
The kids came. First was Nevada, who died due to sudden infant death syndrome at the
age of ten weeks. They ended up having a set of twins and triplets, making the surviving
children between the pair five.
The couple split in 2008 with joint custody of the children, and Musk would go on to date
and marry Talulah Riley. The second marriage ended up in divorce again, but the two
decided to give it another trial by tying the knot for the second time but ultimately parting
ways again. Musk then dated Amber Heard, but the two lasted only a year due to their
intense schedules.
By 2018, Musk had been confirmed to be involved with Grimes, meaning Musk was
going back to his roots again as the artiste is Canadian. The pair have a baby together
called X but have become semi separated, although Musk recently claimed they lived
together.
One remarkable thing about all Musk's relationships is that he maintains a cordial
relationship with all his exes. For example, Musk said he and Amber Heard remains
close friends and love one another and who knows what the future holds.
And after their second and final divorce, Riley still had positive things to say about her
billionaire ex. She even made an appearance during the Strauss Rolling Stone profile of
Musk and told People magazine that she and Musk saw each other all the time and took
care of each other.
Coming back to Justine, Musk's first wife, she recently spoke about Musk where she
dropped more than a few bombshells that will change your view of the industrialist!
Previously, shortly after her divorce, Justine wrote that she watched herself slowly take
the back seat to Musk's work as Musk's success rose astronomically. She became the
trophy wife, which apparently didn't sit well with her.
But as a courtside observer to Musk's insane climb to fame, and with her skills as a
writer, Justine was able to distill the changes in her husband. While responding to a
question on Quora, she gave a rather candid impression of the man she was married to
for eight years. According to her, people like her former husband, Bill Gates, Steve
Jobs, and Richard Branson, who has a friendship with Musk, tend to be freaks and
misfits who were forced to experience the world in an unusually challenging way!
Justine claimed they don't think the way other people think but see things from angles
that unlock new ideas and insights! Other people consider them insane!
Justine illustrated Musk's childhood with the example of another friend who had a
troubled childhood because other kids mocked him for not being cool, a personae Musk
would later embrace, as you shall see! The friend's growing up was terrible enough that
he didn't want other kids going home with him from school because they threw soda
cans at him! So instead of hanging out with these mean kids, Justine's friend buried
himself in computer games and coding, leading him to his first company, which he sold
when he was in his mid twenties! But of course, nobody can throw cans at him again!

snippet.title: PETIÇÃO CONTRA AMBER HEARD CHEGA A 1 MILHÃO DE ASSINATURAS E VIRA PESADELO PARA A WARNER
snippet.description:
Pablo Peixoto do Qu4tro Coisas fala sobre a petição pela demissãod a atriz Amber Heard ede Aquaman 2. Como a Warner Bros deve agir agora? 

Uma petição para remover Amber Heard do Aquaman 2 chega a mais de 900 mil assinaturas. Heard apareceu pela primeira vez como  Mera, a princesa de Xebel , um dos reinos subaquáticos, na Liga da Justiça de Zack Snyder em 2017. Ela repetiu seu papel ao lado de Jason Momoa em Aquaman de 2018  ,  agora o filme DC de maior bilheteria de todos os tempos. Heard está programado para retornar para Aquaman 2 em 2022.

Heard ultimamente tem sido o centro de uma polêmica com o ex-marido Johnny Depp. Depp e Heard, que se conheceram no set do filme The Rum Diary de 2011 , se casaram na ilha particular de Depp nas Bahamas em 2015. Depois de pedir o divórcio em 2016, Heard obteve uma ordem de restrição contra Depp, acusando-o de abusar física e verbalmente dela. Outras acusações contra o ator incluíram Depp tentando fazer com que Heard fosse demitido de Aquaman e impedi-la de ser contratada em outros projetos da Warner Bros. Todas as alegações preocupantes levaram a críticas sobre Depp ter sido escalado como Grindelwald nos filmes Fantastic Beasts em 2016. Depp processou Heard por difamação em 2019, depois que ela escreveu um artigo para o The  Washington Postalegando ter sido vítima de violência doméstica durante seu casamento de curta duração. Depp também processou a publicação britânica The Sun  depois que eles o chamaram de "espancador de mulheres" em um de seus artigos. O caso foi a julgamento em julho, e na segunda-feira passada o juiz decidiu contra Depp, afirmando que ele desmentia que havia evidências suficientes para apoiar as alegações de Heard. Pouco depois, Depp anunciou que foi convidado a renunciar ao Fantastic Beasts 3 , com o estúdio confirmando que ele seria reformulado.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Booed And Humiliated As Her Show Flops…
snippet.description:
Amber Heard was booed and embarrassed as her show bombarded on premiere night. The entertainer got substantial booing from the group as she made that big appearance for her new theater creation "London Fields". Heard was one of a few entertainers featured in the new dramatic variation of Martin Amis' 1989 novel, however, they were met by an ensemble of noisy sneers. Entertainer Amber Heard was booed and embarrassed as her show bombarded on premiere night. In a video of the play's first presentation, one lady can be heard yelling: "Get off!" as Heard strolls onto the stage at London's West End Theater, while another crowd part hollers: "Boo!".

snippet.title: Video shows 'Amber Heard beat up her sister Whitney', High Court told
snippet.description:
Whitney Henriquez was accused of lying under oath about whether her sister was violent towards her after the video was shown to the High Court on Friday.

It showed friends of Ms Henriquez gathered with her around a poolside, asking whether her sister had beaten her up and looking at apparent bruises on her face and chest.

Ms Henriquez was accused on Friday of falsely denying that Ms Heard had ever hit her so as to bolster her sister’s claim she was not violent and was the victim in her marriage to Johnny Depp.

The last-minute emergence of the video, filmed for a reality TV show in 2006 or 2007, came in the libel case the Hollywood star has brought against the publisher of The Sun newspaper for labelling him a ‘wife beater’.

Read the full story here: https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/07/24/johnny-depp-libel-trial-amber-heard-accused-beating-younger/

snippet.title: Richard Dawkins and Amber Heard in Conversation
snippet.description:
World-renowned author and scientist Richard Dawkins, whose passion for the wonders of science and the vital importance of reason has inspired millions of admirers, took part in an unscripted conversation with distinguished guests, tackling a wide variety of compelling topics spanning science, religion, and more.

Actress, activist, and outspoken atheist Amber Heard, critically acclaimed star of films such as Aquaman, Justice League, Her Smell, and Friday Night Lights, will join Prof. Dawkins at the Ikeda Theater. She has served as a Human Rights Champion at the United Nations Human Rights Office and worked with organizations such as the American Civil Liberties Union, the Syrian American Medical Society, Amnesty International, Smile Train, and Planned Parenthood.

This talk took place on October 16th, 2019.

snippet.title: Sophie Turner FINALLY REPLACING Amber Heard in Aquaman 2?!
snippet.description:
The filming of the second movie for DC Extended Universe film Aquaman 2 started filming a couple of months ago, but have fans finally gotten over the fact that Warner Brothers recast Amber Heard as Queen Mera? Absolutely not. As you all remember, when the news of Amber Heard reprising a main role in the previous blockbuster hit came out, lots of fans were outraged, and many even went as far as signing a petition for Warner Bros. to fire the actress, and by “many”, we mean 1.6 million people. That’s a lot! But it is kind of safe to say that all those efforts went nowhere. The actress still landed the important role, and she has been flaunting all her training in social media. Not cool, Amber. But anyway, up until now, fans couldn’t accept the fact that the very same production company who kicked out Johnny Depp from his supposedly upcoming third installment of the Fantastic Beasts series, had decided to keep Amber who was apparently as much involved as Johnny in their ongoing lawsuit. Now, fans are rooting for various other artists to replace Amber Heard from her role as Queen Mera. A lot of fans are throwing their own bets on social media, but we could all agree that one of them really stands out from the crowd. And that celebrity is none other than the Queen of the North herself, Sophie Turner. But what makes Sophie Turner the perfect replacement as Queen Mera? Here are the top three reasons why Sophie can very much dethrone Amber from Aquaman 2. But before that, make sure to hit that subscribe button first and ring that notification bell for more updates. So, let’s begin!

Following the ruckus brought about by their previous marriage, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard’s careers were expected to crumble as they continuously face allegations and suit cases here and there. As Johnny Depp lost his libel case filed against news publisher The Sun in 2020, he also lost his chance to reprise the role of Grindelwald in the upcoming third installment of Fantastic Beasts. But despite Johnny leaving, or being forced rather, to vacate his role, Amber Heard was set to continue on to reprise her role as Queen Mera in the upcoming second installment of the DCEU movie Aquaman 2, entitled Aquaman and The Lost Kingdom. Both movies are set to premiere in 2022, and both movies are going to be under Warner Brothers. 

Even though it has long been decided that Amber Heard would in fact reprise her role, fans are still hoping that Warner Brothers will soon change their mind. However, despite the production company’s rogue decision to keep Amber Heard, which might actually cause their new upcoming movie to flop, at least they are somehow trying to reduce Amber Heard’s exposure.

1. She rocks red locks
Queen Mera is a pretty and strong minded redhead who rules Atlantis. If there’s anyone who quickly comes to mind when talking about redheads, superheroes, kingdom leaders, and action, then there’s only one obvious option: the Queen of the North herself, Sophie Turner. Sophie made her acting debut in the widely-popular HBO series Game of Thrones, and it helped her skyrocket to fame. 

2. Sophie Turner is no newbie to action and superhero scenes
In fact, Sophie actually debuted in this kind of environment. Remember, she debuted her acting skills as a teenager in HBO hit Game of Thrones, and it brought her career to unimaginable heights. Her character, Sansa Stark, initially started off as a naive young woman, but when the time came that her family suffered from one cruelty and betrayal after another, she grew up hardened and stronger than ever. Exactly what we are looking for in a Queen Mera. 

3. Queen Mera is the new superhero role that Sophie Turner needed
First of all, there is a certain stereotype going on around women that once a lady becomes a mother, she cannot take on strong roles anymore. Well, Sophie is the perfect female to break this barrier in the film industry. Sophie gave birth last year to her lovely daughter with Jonas Brothers’ member Joe Jonas. The actress still keeps updating her social media showcasing her siren physique that is perfect for Queen Mera. Also, it’s a little unfortunate for talented actors such as Sophie to get shackled to roles that underserve them or weak franchises that drag them down. 

Despite all these obvious choices, Warner Brothers still stuck with their initial decision to keep Amber Heard and keep her in the spotlight. 

That’s all for today, we hope you enjoyed that video, and if you did, don’t forget to like, subscribe, and hit that notification bell for more videos like this. Don’t forget to check out our video, “Actresses who can replace Amber Heard in Aquaman 2” as well. Stay tuned!

snippet.title: Amber Heard: Cosmetic Surgery and Facial analysis (2020)
snippet.description:
Today I will be doing a cosmetic analysis of the stunning Amber Heard. She is considered to have one of the most perfect faces in Hollywood. Is her face natural, or did she get Cosmetic procedures done? I will show what I found behind all the rumors and speculation, through researching hundreds of photos, and using my knowledge of the world of Plastic Surgery. #AmberHeard #loreal #JohnnyDepp
Amber Heard is an American actress, age 34, born April 22, 1986, to her family in Austin Texas.Today, Amber is an internationally known star, and has been featured in many highly successful films such as: Aquaman ($1.148 Billion USD Worldwide Gross),Justice league ( $657 million USD Worldwide),  Magic Mike XXL ($117 million Worldwide Gross), and some other films like the Rum Diary and Pineapple express. Amber Heard has a current net worth of $9 million Dollars.

Amber heard has also been the face of many Brand/ Ad campaigns through her career. Some examples are: L’Oreal campaign in 2019-Now. In the past she was the face of Guess Girl Belle, a fragrance by Guess fragrance is 2013 and 2014. Recently L’Oreal has been pressured to drop her as the face of the campaign due to alleged abuse toward Johnny Depp. Currently they are in court over allegations, speaking with many divorce lawyers, and presenting their evidence in court. 


Aside from her acting career, Amber is known for her beauty, and is considered to have one of the most perfect faces in the world according to the Greek Golden Ratio. Some say she has a striking resemblance to Scarlett Johansson. Amber touts Near perfect facial symmetry, Large beautiful Eyes, and a cute pointed chin. She also appears to have quite flawless skin, and most certainly has a great skin routine. 


The beginning of Amber Heard’s career, she was very natural, and did not start to change until somewhere in mid 2008. tHe biggest differences are that her face became less soft and round, and began to take shape and become tighter and flatter. This look is most often achieved through buccal fat removal aka a Bichectomy. If it were weight loss, the difference would be even over her entire face, later in her 20’s and much more gradually than 1 year. 


The next procedure was her nose, which was naturally straight and symmetrical. Over studying 100 photos, I saw that her nose was narrowed and nostrils brought in with a rhinoplasty. She most likely tried to hide it by dying her hair brown, a very typical diversion tactic in Hollywood. 


Amber Heard's teeth were her next target for change. In early years, she had, what we call in dentistry, An overjet where teeth jut forward. She probably fixed this problem with invisalign braces that are clear, plastic and not very obvious. She has also been using Teeth Bleaching throughout her career.

The last procedure I am covering is her cheeks. They started out flatter, but still naturally gorgeous and didn’t necessarily need larger cheeks at all. It puzzled many people when she opted to get large cheek implants in 2018 causing a lot of buzz. She also may have lost some weight, further exposing the cheek implants and making them more obvious. A solution would be some dermal filler or Placing some fat around them to make it more subtle. Either way, she is absolutely stunning. 

Right now, Amber Heard and Johnny Depp are in a legal battle over allegations toward each other. I have chosen not to take a stance on the situation and instead am focusing solely on her appearance and some bits about her career. I hope you Understand.

Please know that although I have a very informed opinion based on my own experience I am not an EXPERT or a Doctor.  Please visit a plastic surgeon for medical advice.

snippet.title: Amber Heard ATTACKS LAPD In Court - They Fight Back…
snippet.description:
Amber Heard ATTACKS LAPD In Court - They Fight Back…

Subscribe to Binge Watch -  http://tiny.cc/bingewatch

WATCH NEXT 👇

Amber Heard Booed And Humiliated As Her Show Flops…

https://youtu.be/Klv09j42dS8

Celebrities Who Spoke Up Against Amber Heard’s Lies

https://youtu.be/w-Cu57KpfFI

Related videos:

LAPD FIGHT BACK against Heard after she ATTACKED THEM in COURT!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WiVdqpuGrMY

AMBER'S SCREWED - LAPD FIGHT BACK against Amber Heard after she ATTACKED THEM In COURT | The Gossipy

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_4WuAfhttYw


The last time we’ve heard something about this crazy fight between Amber Heard and Johnny Depp, it was announced that Johnny had a major victory by winning the last court. However, it seems like Amber Heard and her legal team are that desperate, so they subpoenaed LAPD over 2016 domestic disturbance incident!
For those who don’t remember, in 2016 Johnny Depp and Amber Heard allegedly had a fight at their LA apartments. Allegedly, there was a heated altercation and Amber was so scared and asked her friends to call 911. Her friends called 911 twice reporting that there was a huge fight and the apartment is absolutely trashed from a knockdown blowout between the volatile couple. Later, Amber Heard and her allies have given evidence in multiple legal cases saying Johnny Depp hurled a phone at her face and trashed their penthouse kitchen during that notorious fight. Amber and friends claimed in court that there were broken candelabras, glass strewn on the floor and red wine sloshed on the walls and carpets. 

Amber Heard and her friends, iO Tillet Wright and Rocky Pennington described in court the entire situation and claimed that Johnny Depp really threatened Amber and she was scared for her life. Rocky Pennington said to judge: "They have a big kitchen island in the middle of the kitchen and on there, there's candles and like fruit and, you know, glass, like jars and vases and things like that. And he just was hitting everything with the wine bottle, just smashing it all off. So, there was fruit on the floor and baskets and, you know, glass bottles and flowers."

As for Amber Heard herself, she said: "We have huge heavy silver candlesticks, candelabra sticks. Those were on the floor broken. Baskets of fruit that we had on the kitchen island. There … fruit everywhere. Baskets on the ground. The containers holding the spoons and forks, kitchen utensils, those were spilled. He broke a lot of glass things that left glass on the floor … when he walked out into the hallway, you could see wine spilled all over the ground and wine on the walls and … and so I knew that at least he had gone through there and was sloshing wine anywhere." 

But when the police actually arrived there was no sign of a crime. As Amber’s friends called 911 twice, there were 2 groups of policemen who arrived. The first two police officers who arrived on the scene said they didn’t remember seeing any such spillages and that there was no visual evidence that a crime had taken place at all. Moreover, we can see this because a bit later Daily Mail released the body cam footage from a second set of officers (who arrived later, the second time) and they had cameras on when they entered Amber Heard and Johnny Depp's former marital home later that night. And according to this bodycam footage, there’s no spilled red wine, no scene of a crime, no violence at all. Moreover, when the police arrived, Amber Heard didn’t look like she was assaulted.

And of course, Johnny Depp and his legal team had to react on the things Amber Heard and here friends said, so Johnny Depp's attorney, Adam Waldman, also claimed that this evidence proves there was never any wrecking spree and that Amber Heard's account of the evening cannot be trusted.

So, now I want to know your opinion. Do you think Amber Heard and her legal team are so desperate that they are trying to do at least something that can help them out? Do you think she is guilty? Let me know your opinion in the comments section down below. And thanks for watching this video and don’t forget to hit that subscribe button.

Amber Heard and her friends, iO Tillet Wright and Rocky Pennington described in court the entire situation and claimed that Johnny Depp really threatened Amber and she was scared for her life. Rocky Pennington said to judge: "They have a big kitchen island in the middle of the kitchen and on there, there's candles and like fruit and, you know, glass, like jars and vases and things like that. And he just was hitting everything with the wine bottle, just smashing it all off. So, there was fruit on the floor and baskets and, you know, glass bottles and flowers."

As for Amber Heard herself, she said: "We have huge heavy silver candlesticks, candelabra sticks. Those were on the floor broken. Baskets of fruit that we had on the kitchen island. There … fruit everywhere. Baskets on the ground. The containers holding the spoons and forks, kitchen utensils, those were spilled. He broke a lot of glass things that left glass on the floor … when he walked out into the hallway, you could see wine spilled all over the ground and wine on the walls and … and so I knew that at least he had gone through there and was sloshing wine anywhere." 

But when the police actually arrived there was no sign of a crime. As Amber’s friends called 911 twice, there were 2 groups of policemen who arrived. The first two police officers who arrived on the scene said they didn’t remember seeing any such spillages and that there was no visual evidence that a crime had taken place at all. Moreover, we can see this because a bit later Daily Mail released the body cam footage from a second set of officers (who arrived later, the second time) and they had cameras on when they entered Amber Heard and Johnny Depp's former marital home later that night. And according to this bodycam footage, there’s no spilled red wine, no scene of a crime, no violence at all. Moreover, when the police arrived, Amber Heard didn’t look like she was assaulted.

And of course, Johnny Depp and his legal team had to react on the things Amber Heard and here friends said, so Johnny Depp's attorney, Adam Waldman, also claimed that this evidence proves there was never any wrecking spree and that Amber Heard's account of the evening cannot be trusted.

So, now I want to know your opinion. Do you think Amber Heard and her legal team are so desperate that they are trying to do at least something that can help them out? Do you think she is guilty? Let me know your opinion in the comments section down below. And thanks for watching this video and don’t forget to hit that subscribe button.

snippet.description:
Amber Heard Booed And Humiliated As Her Show Flops…

Amber Heard Faces Prison After This…

Related videos:

Heard BOOed as her SHOW FLOPS and the PUBLIC BACKS DEPP!
https://youtu.be/iAK80fPYwHA


Amber Heard has zero chances of making people believe her she was a victim. Now, the tables have turned and recently Amber Heard failed big time! L’Oreal Paris invited Amber Heard to model for the Le Defile L'Oreal Paris Womenswear Spring/Summer 2022 on Paris Fashion Week. But Johnny Depp’s fans were not happy to see her there so they booed her!
The annual Paris Fashion Week is back and better than ever as the designer presentations hit the streets of Paris. The event began on September 28 and closed on October 6. This event is always amazing, glamorous and so many fashionistas and influencers are looking forward to it. As always, the iconic fashion event continued to host an array of famous faces dressed to impress in their best attires. From Oscar-winning actress Helen Mirren to the most recent Cinderella, Camilla Cabello, the event had a seat for everybody at its table. But there was someone who was not really wanted to be seen… everywhere. Yes, that’s Amber Heard who we are talking about.
Ever since Amber Heard began her vicious Johnny Depp career ruining plan, people all over the world want her to be sued, punished and closed in prison. She literally ruined Johnny Depp’s life and career and many people think that’s unfair that someone like Amber Heard keeps on getting roles, having fun and being invited to really special events like Paris Fashion Week.
Just before showing up at such a huge event, Amber Heard took to Twitter and shared a photo of herself getting her hair and makeup done as the cosmetics and skincare giant L’Oréal Paris celebrates the 50th anniversary of its slogan "Because you’re worth it." In the photo, portions of Amber Heard's blonde hair are wrapped around brushes as a team of hairstylists blow-dries her tresses.
"It takes an army (of hair brushes). BTS from @lorealparisUSA @loreal lorealparis 50yearsofworth worthit," Amber Heard captioned the photo, without mentioning when the image was taken. And guess what, Amber Heard was mocked by some Twitter users just for posting this photo! 
Someone accused her of sharing sharing a pic from 2019, posting side-by-side images of the actress before and after getting ready. "Not Amber Heard posting backstage photos from Sep 2019 w/L’Oreal to make it seem like she is relevant and working in 2021. Girl, your jewelry told on you," the person wrote. But the person was absolutely wrong…
In a follow-up post, Amber Heard shared a video of herself talking about the famous L'Oréal tagline. "50 Years Of Worth is an anthem of action," she says in the clip. "It's an anthem of our power, our importance, our value, and a reminder that it's worth fighting for." And of course, this one was also attacked by mulriple Johnny Depp’s fans.
But what about Amber Heard’s appearance on Paris Fashion Week? Well, her appearance on the most amazing event of the fall in Europe has left fans raging. Amber Heard hit the runway on October 3, alongside Mirren for “Le Defile L’Oreal Paris Womenswear Spring/Summer 2022." Amber Heard wore a baby pink jumpsuit with feathered slitted sleeves and a deep neckline, complete with floaty drape details stemming from the waist. Yes, let’s be honest, she looked good! But despite the fact that she looked good, fans were there not to estimate her looks. 
While the actress rocked the runway, many were left wondering how she had been allowed to attend in the first place. Well, it is well-known that Amber Heard has been L’Oréal Paris face and ambassador for a while now. And people are said to be disappointed that Amber Heard remains a spokesperson for beauty brand L'Oreal. She was among the brand representatives who walked the runway on Sunday. And it’s not the first time when L’Oreal Paris shows their support to Amber Heard. When it became clear that Amber Heard was the one, who abused, L’Oréal Paris posted a picture of Heard as part of their WomenMakeCinema series. And the company described Amber Heard as an actress who “highlights that a woman’s inner beauty is what we should value the most.”
But many fans / followers of L’Oréal’s page were quick to point out the absurdity of supporting an abuser, let alone to portray her as an empowering role model for women. And fans even went that far so they called for a boycott to the brand, threatening to never buy L’Oréal (or their affiliate brand, Maybelline) again.

snippet.title: Amber Heard - Rare Photos | Lifestyle | Childhood | Family | Friends
snippet.description:
Amber Laura Heard was born in Austin, Texas, to Patricia Paige Heard (Parsons), an internet researcher, and David C. Heard (David Clinton Heard), a contractor. She has English, Irish, Scottish, German, and Welsh ancestry.

Heard appeared in the Academy Award-nominated film, North Country (2005), in which she played Charlize Theron's character in flashbacks. Her other early film credits include: Syrup (2013), Drive Angry (2011) 3D, The Joneses (2009), Never Back Down (2008), Alpha Dog (2006) and Friday Night Lights (2004). On television, Heard starred on The CW drama, Hidden Palms (2007), and had guest starring roles on Showtime's Californication (2007) and CBS's Criminal Minds (2005)

In 2009, Heard starred in the box office hit, Zombieland (2009), opposite Woody Harrelson, Bill Murray and Jesse Eisenberg. She also starred in the suspense thriller, The Stepfather (2009), with Sela Ward, Dylan Walsh and Penn Badgley. In 2008, she garnered attention for her role in the comedic hit, Pineapple Express (2008), with Seth Rogen and James Franco. Heard received a 2008 Young Hollywood Award for her breakthrough performance in "Pineapple Express".

She appeared in The Rum Diary (2011), opposite Johnny Depp, and John Carpenter's The Ward (2010), which premiered at the 2010 Toronto Film Festival. She also starred in the independent film, And Soon the Darkness (2010), in which she additionally served as a co-producer.

Heard starred in Paranoia (2013), opposite Harrison Ford, Liam Hemsworth and Gary Oldman. The film was released by "Relativity Media" on August 16, 2013. She also starred in Robert Rodriguez's Machete Kills (2013), which was released by "Open Road Films" on March 4, 2013, and McG's 3 Days to Kill (2014), opposite Kevin Costner and Hailee Steinfeld, which was released in 2014.

Additionally, her film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), which premiered at the 2006 Toronto Film Festival, was released by The Weinstein Co. in theaters in the fall of 2013.

Heard resides in Los Angeles, where she is actively involved with Amnesty International. In 2015, she married actor Johnny Depp.

She also starred in the suspense thriller, The Stepfather (2009), with Sela Ward, Dylan Walsh and Penn Badgley. In 2008, she garnered attention for her role in the comedic hit, Pineapple Express (2008), with Seth Rogen and James Franco. Heard received a 2008 Young Hollywood Award for her breakthrough performance in "Pineapple Express".

She appeared in The Rum Diary (2011), opposite Johnny Depp, and John Carpenter's The Ward (2010), which premiered at the 2010 Toronto Film Festival. She also starred in the independent film, And Soon the Darkness (2010), in which she additionally served as a co-producer.

Heard starred in Paranoia (2013), opposite Harrison Ford, Liam Hemsworth and Gary Oldman. The film was released by "Relativity Media" on August 16, 2013. She also starred in Robert Rodriguez's Machete Kills (2013), which was released by "Open Road Films" on March 4, 2013, and McG's 3 Days to Kill (2014), opposite Kevin Costner and Hailee Steinfeld, which was released in 2014.

Additionally, her film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), which premiered at the 2006 Toronto Film Festival, was released by The Weinstein Co. in theaters in the fall of 2013.

Heard resides in Los Angeles, where she is actively involved with Amnesty International. In 2015, she married actor Johnny Depp.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Granted Amber Heard's Phone Records
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp's legal team has been granted access to Amber Heard's phone. snippet.title: Amber Heard HOT Scenes in London Fields (2018)
snippet.description:
Amber Heard all  Hot Seductive scenes in London Fields 2019

London Fields is a 2018 mystery thriller film directed by Mathew Cullen with a screenplay by Roberta Hanley and Martin Amis, based on the 1989 novel of the same name by Amis. The film stars Billy Bob Thornton as Samson Young, a terminally ill writer who has suffered from writer's block for 20 years. The cast also includes Amber Heard, Jim Sturgess, Theo James, Cara Delevingne and Jaimie Alexander.

snippet.description:
Amber Heard Tries Avoiding Jail After Having A Child

Subscribe to Binge Watch -  http://tiny.cc/bingewatch

WATCH NEXT 👇

Related videos :

Amber Heard Shares Video Of Not So Newborn Baby?

https://youtu.be/eoJzY6B4WaQ

Amber Heard's Apology Video - "I Can't Go Behind Bars Now with A Child" (IG LIVE)

https://youtu.be/M3pSG8v3lEE

The Johnny Depp and Amber Heard drama is far from over, and it seems that more and more different details and information are emerging every day. Infamous audio leak, police officers’ bodycam footage, and many other things were revealed during this never-ending legal battle. However, as you may have noticed, all this evidence is strongly against Amber Heard. Except this one. The recent one. A few weeks ago, Amber Heard secretly welcomed her baby girl Oonagh Paige via surrogate. And now fans (and not only fans, literally everyone) sure that Amber will try to use the child to her advantage - to win a lawsuit against Johnny Depp.
It’s been years since the nasty and messy drama started getting really tense between Amber Heard and Johnny Depp. Whether you wanted that or not, you’ve heard about so many plot twists in this ugly divorcing scenario, so it is difficult to surprise you with something unique about the entire situation. According to the recent news and updates, 6 months ago Johnny Depp lost his libel case. Johnny Depp and his legal team tried to fight but there was no chance of winning. Though Johnny Depp has strong support from his fans, things certainly haven't gone JDs way in the courtroom.
As for now, even despite the fact that Johnny’s appeal was rejected by the Court of Appeals in March, a separate lawsuit against Amber Heard in the United States is scheduled to go to trial in April 2022. And also, the good news for the actor is that a judge has finally ruled in his favor when it comes to questions over the $ 7 million divorce settlement Johnny Depp had paid Amber Heard after the couple officially divorced in 2016. At the time, Amber Heard pledged to donate the entire settlement to the American Civil Liberties Union and Children's Hospital Los Angeles, but it wasn’t officially proven. 
Johnny Depp's lawyer Andrew Caldecott says that this public pledge made by Heard was nothing more than a "calculated and manipulative lie," meant only to tip the scales "against Mr. Depp from the very beginning." He has introduced evidence to support his claims, alleging that the Children's Hospital Los Angeles wrote to Johnny Depp's business adviser in 2019 and informed them that Amber Heard still hadn't donated the money. And there are so many things that Amber said or did that still remain controversial or questionable. 
It's obviously been a very messy legal battle, but a good portion of the public seem to believe Johnny Depp's version of events. That is why it seems like Amber Heard has been worried lately and she didn’t know how to make another plot twist. But here we go. Recently, Amber Heard literally shocked the whole world when she revealed she is a mom!
Yes, mom! Out of nowhere, Amber Heard took to IG and shared a photo of herself with a little child, captioning: “I’m so excited to share this news with you. Four years ago, I decided I wanted to have a child. I wanted to do it on my own terms,” she wrote. “I now appreciate how radical it is for us as women to think about one of the most fundamental parts of our destinies in this way. I hope we arrive at a point in which it’s normalized to not want a ring in order to have a crib.”
She added, “A part of me wants to uphold that my private life is none of anyone’s business. I also get that the nature of my job compels me to take control of this. My daughter was born on April 8, 2021. Her name is Oonagh Paige Heard. She’s the beginning of the rest of my life.”
A source exclusively told Page Six on Thursday that Heard is “beyond in love” with her daughter, Oonagh Paige, whom she named after her late mom, Paige. Also, Amber's friends revealed that Oonagh was born with the help of a surrogate after Amber Heard was told she would never be able to carry her own baby. A source who knows the star told us: “Oonagh is absolutely gorgeous, and Amber is besotted. She always knew that she wanted to be a mom, and this is her greatest wish come true. She’s so grateful to the wonderful woman who helped bring Oonagh into her life.” “The most important thing for Amber is that she’s open about Oonagh’s birth,” the source continued.

#divorce #podcast #lawyer 
⭐Follow Jill Coil: https://www.instagram.com/jillcoil/
🎧 Listen to Podcast: https://rss.com/podcasts/noonediesfromdivorce/
📕 Link to Book: https://www.amazon.com/No-One-Dies-Divorce-Marriage-ebook/dp/B091Y8HP67

Sterling R. Swank was born in Utah but had the opportunity to live all over the country including time spent in Tennessee, Georgia, Washington state, and most recently in Iowa. Sterling received his bachelor’s degree in Philosophy from the University of Utah. After graduating from the U he packed up his bags and moved to the Midwest. Three years later he received his Juris Doctorate from Drake University Law School in Des Moines, Iowa.

After graduating from law school, Sterling made the trip back to Utah and joined the Utah State Bar in 2019 and then CoilLaw as an Associate Attorney shortly after. Prior to becoming a part of the CoilLaw team, Sterling worked in the Drake Legal Clinic providing legal services for criminal defense clients and to young people facing juvenile delinquency charges.

Sterling has a passion for the legal system and ensuring the best outcomes for his clients and their families. In his off-time Sterling loves spending time outdoors camping, hiking, or taking a scenic ride on his motorcycle.

The case is interesting because these types of cases happen sometimes, but it is usually a female filing an abuse claim against a male, and here it’s swapped.

Amber Heard (Aquaman) and Johnny Depp started dating in 2012 after The Rum Diary movie (2011). Depp has 2 children from a previous marriage. Johnny’s exes (Vanessa Paradis and Winona Ryder) both came out saying that these abuse claims were totally out of character for Johnny for what they knew of him.

Divorce was finalized in 2017. Heard received 7 million dollars, which she apparently donated to charity. Depp has shown a history of being irresponsible with money. They both agreed they wouldn’t say anything disparaging about the other party. This is a standard agreement in most divorces.

He sued her for libel, and then she came out with a lot of allegations against him.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Shows Off Baby Daughter's Face In New Video
snippet.description: Amber Heard is giving us a better look at her baby girl! The 35-year-old actress shared an adorable video of her daughter, Oonagh, on Instagram on Tuesday. In the video, the “Aquaman” star is holding onto her baby as she tries a green juice. Oonagh looks precious wearing a beige onesie with rainbows on it as she looks around the room. “You can take the gal out of LA, but you can’t take LA out of the gal #notajuicer,” Amber captioned the post. This is the first video Amber has shared of her daughter since she announced her birth last Thursday. “My daughter was born on April 8, 2021. Her name is Oonagh Paige Heard. She’s the beginning of the rest of my life,” she wrote on Twitter.

snippet.title: Amber Heard ATTACKS LAPD In Court - They Fight Back
snippet.description: Johnny Depp last November lost his court case against a British newspaper that called him a “wife beater” and claimed there was “overwhelming evidence” that he had assaulted the actress Amber Heard repeatedly during their marriage. Mr. Depp’s assaults included head-butting Ms. Heard, repeatedly hitting her and tearing out clumps of her hair, wrote Andrew Nicol, the British judge who heard the case, in a ruling issued online. In dismissing the case, he said the defendants had shown that what they published was “substantially true.” The assaults “must have been terrifying,” the judge wrote regarding incidents in March 2015 in Australia, in which Ms. Heard said that Mr. Depp assaulted her several times, including smashing a telephone beside her face. “I accept that Mr. Depp put her in fear of her life,” the judge wrote. Don’t forget to watch today’s video in full to learn the full scoop behind the judge losing it after Amber Heard begs for the case to get thrown out again!

Amber Heard FURIOUS AT Johnny Depp Calling Her Out On Live TV - VOWS TO GET REVENGE | The Gossipy

https://youtu.be/4uwjYXZ_Zi8


It is a pattern. Every time Johnny Depp speaks at any public event, Amber Heard posts something on her social media. This time response from Amber Heard came only a few hours after Johnny Depp had decried ‘cancel culture’ before receiving San Sebastian’s top prize. Was it a coincidence? Or Amber Heard can’t stand the idea that JD is still loved by millions of people?
It seems like Johnny Depp and Amber Heard’s legal battle has taken another place to fight each other. Not in a court, but in real life and on social media. And Amber Heard is yet again the one who attacks JD for no reason! 
On September 22 Johnny Depp was invited to the San Sebastian Film Festival to receive a Donostia Award. It is great to know that although the entire Hollywood is boycotting him, Johnny still manages to get some awards during such difficult times! To list all the awards and nominations Johnny Depp has received in the past, we need to create another video, so let me just mention that he is a living legend!
His career started at the age of 21 as one of Freddy Krueger’s victims in A Nightmare on Elm Street (1984), and over the years, a relationship with the audience crystallized in the early 90s with his lead roles in multiple movies. But his biggest role ever is undoubtedly, a Captain Jack Sparrow! There’s no person alive who doesn’t like this crazy and funny captain! Johnny Depp has played writers, undercover cops or outlaws, almost always misfits, and he has actually starred with the most famous actors ever! Like Penélope Cruz, Kate Winslet, Morgan Freeman, Michelle Pfeiffer, Leonardo Di Caprio, Angelina Jolie, and many, many others! But now… Even for all his merits and roles, his life has unpredictably changed, due to the legal fight with his ex-wife Amber Heard and Hollywood took the position of boycotting the actor, because he was slandered and called a ‘wife beater’.
You all already know this story, so we won’t be repeating it again, so let’s jump straight to the latest updates on JD’s life and career. It's been the third time Johnny Depp visited the Festival following his fleeting appearance in 1998 with Terry Gilliam, and his visit in 2020 for the participation of Crock of Gold: A Few Rounds with Shane MacGowan. Every time JD appears on public events, he makes his fans crazy about him, and this time around his speech literally left the crowd stunned. 
After he took the stage and the audience greeted him with a thunderous ovation, Johnny began his speech talking about his battered reputation and condemned cancel culture amid his ongoing legal woes with his ex-wife, Amber Heard. Due to the fact that Hollywood is currently boycotting him, Johnny Depp said that ‘no one is safe’ and stated: “It can be seen as an event in history that lasted for however long it lasted, this cancel culture, this instant rush to judgment based on what essentially amounts to polluted air”.
Trailing off again while, presumably, looking for the right words, he shifted a bit, expressing that in his opinion, “It’s so far out of hand now that I can promise you that no one is safe. Not one of you. No one out that door. No one is safe.” “It takes one sentence and there’s no more ground, the carpet has been pulled. It’s not just me that this has happened to, it’s happened to a lot of people.”
“This type of thing has happened to women, men. Children have suffered from various types of unpleasantries. Sadly, at a certain point they begin to think that it’s normal. Or that it’s them. When it’s not.”
“I believe that if you are armed with the truth, then that’s all you need,” he continued. “It doesn’t matter if a judgement…has taken some artistic license,” he chuckled, perhaps referencing his unsuccessful bid to overturn a judge’s ruling in his U.K. libel case.

snippet.title: AMBER FIRED FROM AQUAMAN - Sophie Turner FINALLY REPLACING Amber Heard in Aquaman 2 | The Gossipy
snippet.description:
AMBER FIRED FROM AQUAMAN - Sophie Turner FINALLY REPLACING Amber Heard in Aquaman 2 | The Gossipy

Did Amber Heard just get booted for Aquaman 2? This would be great news to Johnny Depp and Aquaman fans around the world. The #FireAmberHeard movement is going strong. It seems the Aquaman 2 director, James Wan, does not even want Amber Heard in the movie. 

Sophia Turner could be replacing Amber Heard as well. Let's what happens.

With the initial court date being pushed back, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard have been given some more time in order to gather more evidence for their individual cases. For quite some time, the two were firing evidence at each other in order to win in court. 

Ever since the recent release of the footage of the LAPD officers from the penthouse night of Amber Heard and Johnny Depp, things have not been looking all too bright for Amber Heard. Her team has been working tirelessly in order to back up her side, however Johnny Depp seems to have made the attempt to strike back.

Amber Heard Now a mother in Between Lawsuits

INTRO: While the entertainment industry has been living up to its name, Fantastic Beasts actor, Johnny Depp, and Aquaman star, Amber Heard’s supporters have been anything but. This has been more so highlighted in the newly taken up role of Heard as a single mother of Baby Oonagh Paige Heard. Yes! A mother! This celebrity news has totally changed the game for Heard in between lawsuits and a number of her supporters have turned against her. 

We will fill you in on the latest Amber Heard motherhood timing cuppa and how this can be of advantage to her losing lawsuit position against Johnny Depp. I hope you all are prepared, and are pumped as we are ready to spill some brewing celebri-tea. Maybe grab some snacks, click the subscribe button, and turn on the notification bell with your Cheetos-covered-finger if you haven’t yet! Now, let’s get on with the video:

To give you a quick timeline rundown, last 2015, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard made headlines when they married in their Los Angeles home. The then couple has touched the hearts of many with their intimate ceremony. However, who would have thought that their divorce and the lawsuits that followed would break the Internet harder than the news of their marriage and even six years later! In 2016, Heard accused Depp of domestic violence and has called for a divorce. Since then, both parties have retaliated with their differing narrative of the same story. Heard has consistently stated in court and in various interviews that Depp had serious substance abuse which would cause him to be violent towards her. Bruised and disturbed Amber would show up in court and vividly recount Depp’s allegedly abusive behavior. 

Depp denied all claims and was strengthened by accounts of his co-stars and supporters. “My husband and I will never forget the sweetness, protection, and kindness he treated me with during every single step of that [pregnancy] process,” Penelope Cruz, Depp’s co-star in ‘Pirates of the Caribbean’ shared in defense of Depp. In the same year, Heard then withdrew her restraining order appeal on the grounds of domestic violence and received a $7 million settlement. 

In 2019, Depp sued Heard for $50 million defamation over a 2018 Washington Post op-ed on which has been pushed, yet again, to next year. “I spoke up against sexual violence — and faced our culture’s wrath. That has to change,” Heard manifested. Especially in this contemporary social climate where a fight for oppressive behaviors is strengthened, her story as a “survivor of domestic abuse” quickly gained an audience. Talking about change, Depp did not brush this off. 

Depp’s lawsuit appealed that Ms. Heard’s allegations of abuse, even with no mentions of Mr. Depp’s name, is false and reflects a perpetrator character. “They were part of an elaborate hoax to generate positive publicity for Ms. Heard and advance her career.”On Ms. Heard’s side of the fence, she pursues a $100 million defamation countersuit against Mr. Depp. The significance of the Depp-Heard controversy has taken the Internet into a whirlwind no one is wanting to miss! While Depp has been continuously dragged by Heard with various accounts of physical and verbal abuse, the Internet is yet to side with her. Videos and phone recordings have surfaced featuring an abusive and manipulative Heard towards her then-husband. “I can’t promise you I won’t get physical again. God, I f---ing sometimes get so mad I lose it,” Heard admitted in a phone recording released in 2020.

snippet.title: Celebrities Who Spoke Up Against Amber Heard’s Lies
snippet.description:
Celebrities Who Spoke Up Against Amber Heard’s Lies
